:'''Mengming:''' Ah, you spotted that we're rather quiet right now. Alright, if there are any aspects of etiquette that you don't understand, ask me, and I'll pick your brains about doing business.
:<!--Custom String Trigger: Wait_Option_502010502_45-->
:<!--Custom String Listener: Wait_Option_502010502_45-->
:{{DIcon|Talk}} What are the rules in tea appreciation?
::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_502105103-->
::'''Mengming:''' It would take forever to explain all the rules. I'll just talk about tea selection and water retention for now.
::'''Mengming:''' Speaking of tea selection, take our Hunter Maofeng tea as an example. The Sleepless Earl only picks the most precious buds, usually long, pointed, and covered in fine hairs.
::'''Mengming:''' As for water retention, tea merchants always say that mineral water is the best &mdash; but the clear and ancient water in Scalegorge Waterscape is the best. There's no better water for tea and alchemy than this.
::'''Mengming:''' I'm also only learning and invite you to call me out if anything I've said is wrong.
:;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
:{{DIcon|Talk}} What made you want to open up a teahouse here?
::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_502105108-->
::'''Mengming:''' My parents opened this teahouse, not me. The Sleepless Earl has been on Starwatcher Avenue for over four hundred years!
::'''Mengming:''' Dad wanted to be near to the port, with all the tired and thirsty people nearby. It was always sure to be a booming business, and we owe all our successes to the kindness of our customers.
:;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
:{{DIcon|Talk}} You are the model of a good young business owner.
::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_502105111-->
::'''Mengming:''' I'm... not young! I'm just at the right age to take over the family business. People may always say we foxians are naturals when it comes to business, but really it's all practice.
::'''Mengming:''' Dad said that he wanted to test me, so he left me the teahouse and wandered off traveling with mom. I'm still a long way off from being proficient in doing business.
::'''Mengming:''' Even now, I still have to ask Mr. Xiyan lots of questions. If you're willing to support me, please be generous with your criticism.
:;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
:{{DIcon|Exit}} I don't have any other questions.
::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_502105115-->
::'''Mengming:''' It's okay. Come back when you've got more time to spare.
::<!--Ends the current performance-->
:'''Mengming:''' It's okay. Come back when you've got more time to spare.
