;(First interaction)
::<!--Trigger PerformanceE 90000069: Config/Level/NPC/W2/NPC_DefaultStory_502010501.json-->
::'''Mengming:''' Welcome to the Sleepless Earl! How many of you are there? Which tea would you like today? My name's Mengming, and this is my teahouse. Let me know if there's anything I can do.
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Any recommendations?
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_502105003-->
:::'''Mengming:''' There's a gentle breeze today, so it's a good time to try our fresh Hunter Maofeng which is in season. We never neglect this tea in our shop, making sure we pick fresh leaves every morning for the afternoon's brew, and afternoon leaves for the evening... ensuring you only drink the freshest.
:::'''Mengming:''' But in this teahouse, we like to ask the customer's preference. Do you like your tea thick and strong, or mild?
:::{{DIcon|Arrow}} I like it strong.
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_502105006-->
::::'''Mengming:''' Ah, then may I suggest the Xianzhou Black Tea? The strength of the tea depends on personal tastes and sensations, but we refuse to serve tea that's too strong and bitter.
::::'''Mengming:''' Drinking tea is for pleasure and not a torment. Since you like it rather strong, then this Xianzhou Black Tea with its red color and slightly astringent taste should suit you perfectly.
:::{{DIcon|Arrow}} I like it mild.
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_502105009-->
::::'''Mengming:''' Then I recommend you try our Vegetations in the Alchemy Cauldron variety. Brew it quickly in a covered cup with boiling water and you'll soon enjoy some tea that's neither thick nor bitter. The flavor is just right.
::::'''Mengming:''' As the saying goes, the freshwater hibiscus is Nature's perfect sculpture. A good mild tea is not bland and tasteless, but mild and not thin. Try a couple of pots and you'll know what I mean.
:::{{DIcon|Arrow}} I'm not fussy at all.
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_502105012-->
::::'''Mengming:''' That's what our fussiest customers are always saying.
::::'''Mengming:''' Okay, let's try sampling a new tea then. This season's new buds of Hunter Maofeng have begun to ripen up. Brew it for a mellow sweet flavor and rich floral bouquet.
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Sorry, I'm not here for tea.
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_502105015-->
:::'''Mengming:''' I see. If you've come to the Sleepless Earl to hear some stories, you're too early &mdash; Xiyan xiansheng isn't ready yet. How about a pot of tea to while away the time?
::<!--Custom String Trigger: TalkSentence_502105016-->
::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_502105016-->
::'''Mengming:''' By the way, if you're on business and in a hurry, we stock a range of cold bottled beverages for you to take away.
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} You've really got the gift of the gab.
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_502105018-->
:::'''Mengming:''' You're too kind. I just started studying commerce and am not good at talking shop. Please forgive me if I ever behaved inappropriately. Every customer here is my teacher, and you are no exception.
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} You won't bully me for not understanding anything about tea, right?
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_502105021-->
:::'''Mengming:''' You flatter me! I inherited this store from my parents, and most of our customers are experts. I don't have any particular skills to show off. Rather, there's much I can learn from our guests here.
::'''Mengming:''' Brewing tea, rules of the tea ceremony... it's all knowledge. Please be generous with your tips and tutelage.
::<!--Custom String Trigger: TalkSentence_502105023-->
::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_502105023-->
::'''Mengming:''' If a customer wants to chat, they have to sit inside... well, is there anything else that you'd like to ask me?
;(Subsequent interactions)
